US cases of vaping lung disease jump to 805 with 12 deaths
US health officials said on September 26th (local time) that US death toll from vaping-related illness hit 12, and cases of vaping lung disease jumped to 805, CNA reported.
The US Center for Disease Control and Prevention reported the figures, and said they had not identified the specific substance that caused the related illness.
However, most patients reported they had used THC-containing vaping products, THC is the main psychoactive compound in marijuana.
It is reported that the lung disease outbreak is related to contaminated vaping atomizers purchased from the black market.
The CDC pointed out that the 12 deaths came from 10 states from California to Florida, while the 805 confirmed and suspected cases were reported by 46 states and the U.S. Virgin Islands.
Over the past 3 weeks, India and the US state of Massachusetts have banned the sale of vaping products, while New York and Michigan have banned flavored ones.
Reports say the Trump administration plans to ban all flavored vaping products with the exception of tobacco flavor from October.
When is the next bus?
"Internet + Smart Stop Signs" tells you.
On the 27th, Nanjing Smart Transportation and Gaode Map announced that the first batch of "Internet + Smart Stop Signs" in China officially landed in Nanjing, which will light up 54 electronic bus screens in the city, which will comprehensively upgrade the level of Nanjing's informatization service, improve the efficiency of bus services and the happiness of people.
In the past, passengers were usually waiting for buses anxiously, which was very common scene at bus stops.
It is difficult to know the bus running time, bus condition and vehicle location along the way, and the problem of bus travel is urgent to be solved, especially in some big cities, the commuting distance is long and the traffic conditions are complicated in the morning and evening rush hours, which makes it difficult to guarantee the punctuality of buses.
